<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="pow" id="pow">pow</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Sintaxe:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">pow</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> base, <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

A função pow() devolve base elevada a exp. Há um erro de domínio (domain error)
se base é zero e exp é menor que ou igual a zero. Há também um erro de domínio
se a base é negativa e exp não é um inteiro. Há um erro de intervalo (range error)
se ocorrer overflow.
</p>

<p>
O C++ também fornece as seguintes formas sobre-carregadas (overload):

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">pow</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">float</span> base, <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a powf() em C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">pow</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> base, <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// igual a powl() em C99</span></pre>
<p>
O C++ também fornece versões sobre-carregadas de pow() que fazem potenciação de inteiros:

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">pow</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">float</span> base, <span class="kw4">int</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">pow</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> base, <span class="kw4">int</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">pow</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> base, <span class="kw4">int</span> <span class="kw3">exp</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
